oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Photograph of Spanish-American War military camp
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Showing soldiers standing outside their tents in camp, probably in Cuba during Spanish-American War deployment. Image may be associated with the service of Capt. Walter M. Fitzgerald of Co. A, 4th Tenn. Inf. Regt., US Volunteers, which was posted to Trinadad, Santa Clara Province, Cuba.
